    "comment": "Rationale: Stimulation of synaptosomes by high potassium (K), induces release of radiolabelled proline. These data indicate depolarization-induced proline release from SVs. The L-proline transporter is expressed in synaptic vesicles (see linked reference annotation). Therefore these data indicate a function of L-proline in transporting proline into SVs.. Experimental description: Male Wistar (WAG) rats weighing 180-220 g were de- capitated, and visual cortex slices",
